<paragraph id="4E70652765C3A56C6D2656CF5093EEA5" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Lectotype</paragraph>
<paragraph id="01CE22070FCBB025639B5BBC7152581D" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
(designated here):-China, Tibet, Panggong Tso, July 25, 1927, 
<emphasis id="34DD4A7EC7BF701D0CA4A36783D62566" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
(Z000002688 digital image!, Figure 
<figureCitation id="9DA43C1A5D58BE7225C7F3ED14B6B6AF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Lectotype of S. pusilla Em. Schmid (Walter Bosshard, Bosshard s. n., Z 000002688)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59527.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489393" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">5</figureCitation>
; Isolectotype: China, Tibet, Panggong Tso, 
<emphasis id="DCD02B64815C3CC01BEF0BB1CDE0CEFB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, Z barcode Z000002689 and Z000002690 digital image!).
</paragraph>
<caption id="519CA9AEAE9614695D1AD564B8FE5135" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.170.59527.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/489393" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
<paragraph id="7A9FAA01E440F894A8DD1858553C7ECE" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis id="F73A18FF7825CF9764A222F3C99E012C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Figure 5.</emphasis>
Lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="475FAB900DB18A8ECAAEE38A8FB659F5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis id="F08437EBEAAD49E1B696BA580DA4F4AC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">S. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Em. Schmid (Walter Bosshard, 
<emphasis id="6D02CBF74A501320EF1FF5A210C4FD2C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, Z000002688).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DA33B9A5C88A30CC84A58EB93EE064D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7B6521C0825628B3AC9F8A769E14FAE9" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="879362A47FF171DC26154B0E8F860086" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">
<taxonomicName id="44EACF141A6FA689E48326BE44B7548D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="S." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis id="2BA8234699E1428D1BE237172C803973" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">S. pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Schmid based on three specimens &quot; 
<emphasis id="6E3A01752F4B63E51036A7E338E4E08E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, 25. VII. 1927; 
<emphasis id="B9C56D2E35D228AED510221711CB5219" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, 29. VII. 1927; 
<emphasis id="CF22EAF53457C8D74CD70BB387EC0A56" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Bosshard s.n.</emphasis>
, 13. VIII. 1927&quot; collected by Bosshard from China, but he 
<normalizedToken id="09101EB075667F97A96FB307A0CC1FE6" originalValue="didn’t">didn't</normalizedToken>
designate one of them as holotype in the protologue. Plants of Central Asia (
<bibRefCitation id="405947CDF8D40F69616A35FA9F6F996A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1201/b10754" author="Grubov, VI" journalOrPublisher="Annales Botanici Fennici" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B4" refString="Grubov, VI, Kozhevnikov, YP, 2007. Plants of Central Asia - Plant Collection from China and Mongolia. Science Publishers, 33 pp. https://doi.org/10.1201/b10754" title="Plants of Central Asia - Plant Collection from China and Mongolia. Science Publishers, 33 pp." url="https://doi.org/10.1201/b10754" year="2007">Grubov and Kozhevnikov 2007</bibRefCitation>
) cited &quot;Panggon Toso July 25, 1927 (typus)&quot;. Yet following Art. 9.6 and Art. 40 Note 1 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="BA65F457D91A9F75EE08EECCE03A4F23" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B15" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prad, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
), none of them can be treated as holotype, but all should be considered as syntypes. Bosshard selected type specimens that were deposited at W and Z (
<bibRefCitation id="95350F560E82E3F8C203342BB0EDE0E2" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103859" refId="B13" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1993. Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103859" title="Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/103859" year="1993">Stafleu and Cowan 1993</bibRefCitation>
). Three original specimens were traced deposited in Z (Z000002688 digital image!, Z000002689 digital image!, and Z000002690 digital image!). All of them agreed with the collection location and date in the protologue and had a label 
<normalizedToken id="752BA8FC20C29FE26EF29E918B2708DF" originalValue="“Typus”">&quot;Typus&quot;</normalizedToken>
and another label &quot;Syntype of 
<taxonomicName id="6B31A7520396D6E240150A74B9EF1C75" authorityName="EM. Schmid, Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 31: 41" authorityYear="1932" class="Gastropoda" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Stellaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stellaria pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis id="E5313BA10B4E8B0D362D3E65F6036C19" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Stellaria pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
EM. Schmid&quot; written by Sallucn at the same time. Given its label &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="D5663576AA04E7A842F49F848E001AB8" authorityName="EM. Schmid, Repert. Spec. Nov. Regni Veg. 31: 41" authorityYear="1932" class="Gastropoda" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Stellaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Stellaria pusilla" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis id="5FC591FA98F617044525C0487231C24D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71">Stellaria pusilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Schmid nov. spes&quot; and its good preservation, the presence of flower and lower part of the plant, Z000002688 is designated here as the lectotype following Art. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="02BCC277CFE8BD8B9A699F20237E51E6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="71" refId="B15" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, WH, Li, DZ, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prad, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
